{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "In the first stage, fetch task dataset, a supervised dataset consisting of input-label pairs is either fetched from the conn2res repository, if the name of the task is provided by the user, or directly loaded if an external path is provided instead.",
    "In the second stage, set connectivity matrix, an instance of a reservoir object is created, and its network architecture and dynamics are set based on the connectivity matrix and the type of local nonlinearity specified by the user, respectively.",
    "In the third stage, simulate reservoir dynamics, the task inputs from the previous stage are introduced as external signals to the reservoir through the set of input nodes specified by the user.",
    "The dynamical models in the con-n2res toolbox simulate the time evolution of the reservoir's internal units (which are activated thanks to the propagation of the external input signals), and generate time series activity for each node in the reservoir.",
    "In the fourth stage, learning, the time series activity of the readout nodes or modules specified by the user are retrieved and passed on to the readout module, together with the task labels from the first stage."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}